8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 201, L.D. 301, “An Act to Allow the
10 Public Utilities Commission to Establish Performance-based Metrics and Rate-adjustment
11 Mechanisms for a Public Utility in Any Proceeding”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Allow the Public Utilities Commission to Use Quantitative Metrics and
14 Rate-adjustment Mechanisms in a Proceeding for a General Rate Increase'
15 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
16 following:
17 'Sec. 1. 35-A MRSA §307, sub-§6 is enacted to read:
18 6. General increase in rates; rate-adjustment mechanisms; quantitative metrics.
19 The commission may establish or authorize rate-adjustment mechanisms or quantitative
20 metrics pertaining to a public utility's operations and activities in a proceeding for a general
21 increase in rates.'
22 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
23 number to read consecutively.
24 SUMMARY
2255 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. It allows the Public Utilities
2266 Commission to establish or authorize rate-adjustment mechanisms or quantitative metrics
2277 pertaining to a public utility's operations and activities in a proceeding for a general
2288 increase in rates.
